Elnusa, Energi Mega, Indo Tambangraya: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-03-16T01:44:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/elnusa-energi-mega-indo-tambangraya-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  fell 1.3 percent to 3,524.48.  Energy companies: Crude oil for April delivery tumbled the
most in nearly five months, falling 4 percent to $97.18 a barrel
in  New York  yesterday. Oil rose 0.7 percent to $97.89 a barrel
in after-hours trading in New York as of 8:43 a.m. Jakarta time.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ), Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, fell 2.6 percent to 2,850 rupiah and
PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest, declined
2.3 percent to 126 rupiah.  Metal producers: Nickel futures fell 4.3 percent to $24,705
a metric ton in  London  yesterday. Tin plunged 4.4 percent to
$28,600 a ton, the most since Nov. 16. PT International Nickel  Indonesia  (INCO IJ), the nation’s largest producer of the metal,
slid 1.1 percent to 4,700 rupiah and PT Timah (TINS IJ), the
nation’s biggest tin producer, lost 1.9 percent to 2,575 rupiah.  PT Elnusa (ELSA IJ): The oil services provider’s 2010 net
income fell to 63.9 billion rupiah ($7.3 million) from 466.2
billion rupiah a year earlier, the company said in a statement
published in Investor Daily Indonesia today. Elnusa was
unchanged at 295 rupiah.  PT Indo Tambangraya Megah (ITMG IJ): The Indonesian unit of  Thailand ’s biggest coal producer will increase its capital
expenditure to $126 million from $110 million this year,
Investor Daily reported, citing Indo Tambangraya Corporate
Secretary Roslini Onwardi. The company will spend the money on
infrastructure development and restoration of its facilities,
the report said. Indo Tambangraya, a unit of Banpu Pcl, rose 3.3
percent to 47,000 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  